 Song Sales Chart|url=http://news.wowtv.co.kr/NewsCenter/News/Read?articleId=A201911130389&t=NN|website=Korea Economic TV|date=November 13, 2019}}</ref> Simultaneously, the single rose eighty-nine spots to number 19 on the [[Gaon Digital Chart]] and topped China's [[QQ Music]] Korean Song chart for two consecutive weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=45&hitYear=2019&termGbn=week|title=Digital Chart \u2013 Week 45 of 2019|website=Gaon Chart|language=ko|accessdate=November 14, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/?ac=article_view&entry_id=1197736|title=(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \u4e2d QQ\ubba4\uc9c1 \ud55c\uad6d\uac00\uc694 \ucc28\ud2b8 2\uc8fc \uc5f0\uc18d 1\uc704\u2026\uae00\ub85c\ubc8c \ub300\uc138 \uc785\uc99d|author=Lee Deok-haeng|website=XSportsNews|language=ko|date=November 14, 2019}}</ref> On December 21, (G)I-dle performed their hit singles at the 2020 Tainan Christmas & New Year Eve Party at [[Tainan|Tainan City]], [[Taiwan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kstarhk.com/9504/\u53f0\u7063\u6f14\u5531\u6703-\uff08g\uff09i-dle\u58d3\u8ef8\u6f14\u51fa\u300c2020\u81fa\u5357\u597dyoung\u8036\u8a95\u8de8\u5e74\u300d/|title=[\u53f0\u7063\u6f14\u5531\u6703] \uff08G\uff09I-DLE\u58d3\u8ef8\u6f14\u51fa\u300c2020\u81fa\u5357\u597dyoung\u8036\u8a95\u8de8\u5e74\u300d\u6f14\u5531\u6703\u71b1HIGH\u767b\u5834(191221)|trans-title=[Taiwan Concert] (G) I-DLE Finale Performs \"2020 Tainan Good Young New Year's Eve\" Concert Hit High (191221)|website=K-Star HK|date=December 22, 2019}}</ref> Their stage was recorded the highest tide of the event of an appearance of 80,000 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.secjie.com.tw/newsview_3713.html|title=\u53f0\u5357\u597dyoung\u8036\u8a95\u8de8\u5e74\u6f14\u5531\u6703\u5168\u5834\u55e8\u7ffb\u5929|language=tw|date=December 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2020: I-Land tour and ''I Trust''===\nOn January 28, 2020, the group announced their first world tour, titled \"I-Land: Who Am I\", which would span 32 different cities around the world.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uae00\ub85c\ubc8c \ud32c \ub9cc\ub09c\ub2e4\u2026\uc138\uacc4 32\uac1c \ub3c4\uc2dc\uc11c \uccab \uc6d4\ub4dc\ud22c\uc5b4|trans-title=(G)I-DLE meet global fan\u2026 First World Tour in 32 Cities of the World|url=https://www.edaily.co.kr/news/read?newsId=01115206625642640&mediaCodeNo=258|website=EDaily|date=January 29, 2020}}</ref> Later, it was announced their commenced show in Bangkok and new album release project in mid-March was postponed in response to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus outbreak]] and to ensure the safety and health of the artist, fans, and staff.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mksports.co.kr/view/2020/153119/|script-title=ko:(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uccab \uc6d4\ub4dc\ud22c\uc5b4 \ubc29\ucf55 \uacf5\uc5f0 \uc77c\uc815 \uc5f0\uae30\u2026\u201c\ucf54\ub85c\ub09819 \ud655\uc0b0 \uc6b0\ub824\u201d|trans-title=(G)I-dle postponed their first World Tour Bangkok show\u2026 \"Concern Spreading Corona 19\"|work=MK Sports|author=Kim Na-young|date=February 14, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportsseoul.com/news/read/888880|script-title=ko:(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uc6d4\ub4dc\ud22c\uc5b4\u00b73\uc6d4 \uc0c8 \uc568\ubc94 \ubc1c\ub9e4 \ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8 \uc7a0\uc815 \uc5f0\uae30[\uacf5\uc2dd]|trans-title=(G)I-dle World Tour, March New album release project tentatively postponed [Official]|work=Spots Seoul|author=Choi Jin-sil|date=February 28, 2020|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\nOn March 26, 2020, (G)I-dle was announced as part of the lineup of the 2020 [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] Stream Aid, scheduled for March 28. The livestream is a 12-hour charity livestream concert aiming to raise money for COVID-19 relief. They are the first female K-pop group to participate.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.twitch.tv/en/2020/03/26/twitch-stream-aid-go-live-to-save-lives-on-328/|title=Twitch Stream Aid: Go live to save lives on 3/28|publisher=[[Twitch (service)|Twitch]]|date=March 26, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/popasia/blog/2020/03/27/you-can-watch-monsta-x-and-gi-dle-twitch-stream-aid-weekend|title=You can watch MONSTA X and (G)I-DLE in Twitch Stream Aid this weekend|publisher=SBS PopAsia|date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 6, 2020 the group released their third EP titled ''[[I Trust]]'' with \"[[Oh my god ((G)I-dle song)|Oh my god]]\" as its lead single.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.khan.co.kr/entertainment/sk_index.html?art_id=202003240739003&sec_id=540101&pt=nv|script-title=ko:[\uacf5\uc2dd] (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uc138 \ubc88\uc9f8 \ubbf8\ub2c8\uc568\ubc94 \u2018I trust\u2019\ub85c 9\uac1c\uc6d4 \ub9cc\uc5d0 \ucef4\ubc31\u20264\uc6d4 6\uc77c \ubc1c\ub9e4 \ud655\uc815|trans-title=[Official] (G)I-DLE comeback in 9 months with third mini album 'I trust'\u2026 April 6 release confirmed|work=KyungHyang Newspaper|author=Yoo In-sun|date=March 24, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbnnews.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=382217|script-title=ko:(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uc804\uc18c\uc5f0 \uc790\uc791\uace1 'Oh my god'\uc73c\ub85c \ucef4\ubc31|trans-title=[Official] (G)I-DLE comeback with Jeon So-yeon's own song \"Oh my god\"|work=NBN News|author=Hong Seung-hoon|date=March 31, 2020}}</ref> The album consists of five songs including an English-language version of the title track.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theceluv.com/article.php?aid=1586162596316145007|script-title=ko:(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, '\ub2f9\ub2f9\ud568'\uc73c\ub85c 9\uac1c\uc6d4 \ub9cc\uc5d0 \ucef4\ubc31\u2026\"\ub450 \uac00\uc9c0 \ubc84\uc804 \ubb34\ub300 \uae30\ub300\"[\uc885\ud569]|work=The Celebrity News|author=Kim He-seo|date=April 6, 2020}}</ref> In conjunction with the release of ''I Trust'', (G)I-dle had signed with [[Republic Records]] to help highlight and push their individuality into the U.S. marketplace.<ref name=\"republic\"/> The album had over 91,311 pre-orders, making it their most pre-ordered EP, and became their highest selling album by selling 100,000 physical copies in three days.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hanteonews.com/ko/article/all?fc=5343|script-title=ko:[\uc77c\uac04\ub7ad\ud0b9: 4\uc6d4 7\uc77c] (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4((G) I-DLE)\uc758 'I TRUST: \ubbf8\ub2c8\uc568\ubc94 3\uc9d1 TRUE VER.' 1\uc704|work=Hanteo|date=April 7, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://star.hankookilbo.com/News/Read/202004081732750778?did=NA&dtype=&dtypecode=&prnewsid=|script-title=ko:(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \ucef4\ubc31 \uc0ac\ud758 \ub9cc \uc74c\ubc18 \ud310\ub9e4\ub7c9 10\ub9cc \uc7a5 \ub3cc\ud30c\u2026\uc790\uccb4 \ucd5c\uace0|trans-title=100,000 albums sold over three days. Self best|publisher=Lee Ho-yeon |language=ko |date=April 8, 2020}}</ref> ''I Trust'' debuted atop the [[Gaon Album Chart]] becoming (G)I-dle's first number-one album in South Korea and achieved their highest-ever position on Billboard's World Albums chart at No. 4.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=202004170100127900007905&servicedate=20200416|script-title=ko:[SC\ucd08\uc810] \"\u7f8e \ube4c\ubcf4\ub4dc 5\uac1c\ucc28\ud2b8 \uac15\ud0c0\"\u2026(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uc5b4\ub5bb\uac8c K-POP \ub300\ud45c \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9\uc774 \ub410\ub098|trans-title=[Focus on SC] \"Swiping 5 Billboards in the US\"\u2026 (G)I-dle, how did you become a representative girl group of K-POP|publisher=Sports Chosun|first=Baek|last=Ji-eun|date=April 16, 2020}}</ref> The music video for \"Oh my god\" broke their personal record by amassing 17 million views within its first day of release.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.g-enews.com/ko-kr/news/article/news_all/202004081105565115c4c55f9b3d_1/article.html?md=20200408112310_R#linkpop|script-title=ko:[\uae00\ub85c\ubc8c-\uc5d4\ud130 24] (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, '\uc544\uc774 \ud2b8\ub7ec\uc2a4\ud2b8(I trust)' \uc544\uc774\ud2a0\uc988 \ud1b1\uc568\ubc94 35\uac1c \uc9c0\uc5ed 1\uc704|trans-title=[Global-Enter 24] (G)I-dle Ranked #1 in iTunes' Top 35 Albums of 'I Trust'|publisher=Global Economic|author=Kim Seong|date=April 7, 2020}}</ref> The song also marked the first time the group has appeared on the [[Official Charts Company|Scottish Singles Chart]] and charted at number 97, becoming only the third K-pop artist and the second female act to appear on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/scottish-singles-chart/20200410/42/|title=Official Scottish Singles Sales Chart Top 100 \u2013 10 April 2020 - 16 April 2020|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|date=April 16, 2020}}</ref> On April 17, 2020, they won their first public broadcast win on [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]]'s ''[[Music Bank (TV series)|Music Bank]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvdaily.asiae.co.kr/read.php3?aid=15871161541536716010|script-title=ko:'\ubba4\uc9c1\ubc45\ud06c' (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uc704\ub108 \uaebe\uace0 1\uc704 \"\uc544\ubb34 \uc870\uac74 \uc5c6\uc774 \uc0ac\ub791\ud574 \uc8fc\uc154\uc11c \uac10\uc0ac\"|publisher=TvDaily|first=Lee|last=Jong-eun|date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Members ==\n* [[Cho Mi-yeon|Miyeon]] (\ubbf8\uc5f0)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&query=%EB%AF%B8%EC%97%B0&sm=ppl_cts&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService&os=8207420|title=Miyeon official 'Naver' profile}}</ref>\n* [[Minnie (singer)|Minnie]] (\ubbfc\ub2c8)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&query=%EB%AF%BC%EB%8B%88&sm=ppl_cts&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService&os=8207418|title=Minnie official 'Naver' profile}}</ref>\n*[[Soojin]] (\uc218\uc9c4)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&query=%EC%88%98%EC%A7%84&sm=ppl_cts&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService&os=8207416|title=Soojin official 'Naver' profile}}</ref>\n* [[Jeon So-yeon|Soyeon]] (\uc18c\uc5f0)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&query=%EC%86%8C%EC%97%B0&sm=ppl_cts&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService&os=3885550|title=Soyeon official 'Naver' profile}}</ref>\n* [[Song Yuqi|Yuqi]] (\uc6b0\uae30)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&query=%EC%9A%B0%EA%B8%B0&sm=ppl_cts&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService&os=8207399|title=Yuqi official 'Naver' profile}}</ref>\n* Shuhua (\uc288\ud654)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&query=%EC%8A%88%ED%99%94&sm=ppl_cts&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService&os=8207395|title=Shuhua official 'Naver' profile}}</ref>\n\n== Philanthropy ==\nOn April 22, 2020, (G)I-dle donated 30,000 bottles of hand sanitizer worth \u20a9100 million through Holt Children's Services for the children and their families to overcome [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Korea|COVID-19 in South Korea]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=202004221344494123050_1|script-title=ko:(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \ucf54\ub85c\ub09819 \uadf9\ubcf5 \uc704\ud574 1\uc5b5 \uc6d0 \uc0c1\ub2f9 \uc190 \uc138\uc815\uc81c 3\ub9cc \uac1c \uae30\ubd80(\uacf5\uc2dd)|publisher=HeraldPop|first=Park|last=Seo-yeon|date=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Artistry ==\n[[File:180908 (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4 (G)I-DLE DMC Festival.png|thumb|right|(G)I-dle in September 2018]]\n\n=== Image ===\n(G)I-dle was praised for their musicality and ambiguity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://star.ohmynews.com/NWS_Web/OhmyStar/at_pg.aspx?CNTN_CD=A0002466220&CMPT_CD=P0010|title=\ub370\ubdd4 3\uac1c\uc6d4\ucc28 (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uc2e0 \uc74c\uc6d0\uac15\uc790\ub85c \uc790\ub9ac\ub9e4\uae40\ud560\uae4c?|author=Son Hwa-sin|date=August 25, 2018|work=OhmyNews}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201809051043500410|title=\u2018\uc74c\uc6d0\ucc28\ud2b8\u2192\uc74c\ubc29 1\uc704\u2019 \uc544\uc774\ub4e4, 5\uac1c\uc6d4\ucc28 \uc548\ubbff\uae30\ub294 \uad34\ubb3c\uc2e0\uc778 \ud589\ubcf4[\ubba4\uc9c1\uc640\uce58]|author=Hwang Hye-jin|date=September 5, 2018|work=Newsen}}</ref> Natalie Morin from [[Refinery29]] described them as individuals with different energies that complements each other.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3132673/gi-dle-interview-self-produced-music-soyeon/|title=Meet (G)I-dle, The Women In K-Pop Who Are Unafraid To Grab The Mic|author=Natalie Morin|date=August 1, 2019|work=[[Refinery29]]}}</ref>  She also described them as \"bold and sensual\", characteristics which she asserts sets them apart from other K-pop girl groups. ''Mor.bo'' named them as a diverse group that is unafraid to try different music styles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ismorbo.com/mor-bo-radar-5-nuevos-grupos-k-pop-que-experimentan-con-edm-hip-hop-y-rb/|title=5 nuevos grupos K-pop que experimentan con EDM, hip hop y R&B|date=August 14, 2019|work=MOR.BO}}</ref> ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]] magazine'' named the group as \"independent musicians and artists\" where girl groups' concepts typically work within a mold that was made by someone else.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.co.kr/article/42660|title=\ud038\ub364, \uc5ec\uc790 \uc544\uc774\ub3cc\uc758 \uc7ac\ubc1c\uacac \uc21c\uac044 \uc5ec\uc790 \uc544\uc774\ub3cc\uc758 '\uc544\ud2f0\uc2a4\ud2b8'\ub85c\uc11c\uc758 \uacbd\uc7c1\uc774 \ube5b\uc744 \ubc1c\ud558\ub294 \uc21c\uac04, \uba4b\uc9d0\uc740 \ub450 \ubc30\ub85c \ud3ed\ubc1c\ud55c\ub2e4|trans-title=5 Scenes of the Rediscovery of Female Idols.|date=October 14, 2019|work=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]}}</ref>\n\nDespite being the youngest group to appear on ''Queendom'', (G)I-dle members were actively involved in their own music videos, jacket photoshoots, song arrangements, choreography, and outfits production.<ref name=\"2nd\">{{cite web|url=https://www.tvreport.co.kr/2014513|trans-title=Second year (G)I-DLE able to turn Queendom upside down|title='\ub370\ubdd4 2\ub144 \ucc28' (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, '\ud038\ub364' \ub4a4\uc9d1\uc5b4\ub193\uc744 \uc218 \uc788\ub358 \uc774\uc720|author=Kim Min-ji|date=October 19, 2019|work=TvReport}}</ref>\n\n=== Musical style ===\nTaylor Glasby from [[MTV]] stated that (G)I-dle songs are steeped in their very essence \u2014 a girl's complex, internal house of mirrors that is constantly being broken, assessed, understood, and remade, where one style or sound is never enough to reflect who they are. (G)I-dle is the enticing tropical beats and coy finger snaps of \"Latata\" and the ominous, warning whistled hook of \"Hann (Alone)\". They are also the pensive harmonies and slow throb of bass on the R&B-infused ballad \"Put It Straight,\" the whimsical words painted over the house music of \"What's In Your House,\" and even the tango of \"Senorita\". Their lyrics push back, they beckon. They can be boring nonchalance or sharpening desire.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3132673/gi-dle-interview-self-produced-music-soyeon/|title=(G)I-DLE ARE 'STANDING OUT' WITH THEIR SELF-PRODUCED SOUND AND DEFINING IT ON THEIR OWN TERMS|date=July 26, 2019|website=MTV News}}</ref>\n\nKim Na-yul writing for [[Herald Corporation|Herald Pop]] described (G)I-dle's genre can only be performed by them and made a good impression on the public.<ref>{{cite web|title=[POP\ucd08\uc810]\"\ud038\ub364 \ucd5c\ub300 \uc218\ud61c\" (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, 'LION' MV \uacf5\uac1c\u2192\uc5f0\uc77c \ud654\uc81c\uc131 \u7532|url=http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=201911042216354818533_1|publisher=HeraldPop|author=Kim Na Yul|date=November 4, 2019}}</ref> ''[[Melon (online music service)|Melon]] magazine'' described (G)I-dle's music generally as \"Uniqueness is (G)I-dle's most powerful weapon.\" crossing genres from \"Latata\" (moombahton), \"Hann (Alone)\" (Eastern European rhythm), \"Senorita\" (Latin pop) and \"Uh-Oh\" (Boom bap).<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.melon.com/musicstory/inform.htm?mstorySeq=9829|title=2019\ub144\uc758 K-POP \ud2b8\ub799 7|date=December 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Stage performance===\nThe group was also praised for their stage presence during performances such as [[Melon Music Awards|2018 MMA]]'s golden stage reminiscent of [[Cleopatra]], and [[2018 Mnet Asian Music Awards|2018 MAMA]]'s stage performing with dozens of female dancers to emphasize the image of women.<ref name=\"HOT\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ize.co.kr/articleView.html?no=2018123100287240092|trans-title=2018 year-end awards ceremony BEST|title=2018 \uc5f0\ub9d0 \uac00\uc694\uc2dc\uc0c1\uc2dd \ubb34\ub300 BEST|author=Park Hee Ah|date=December 31, 2018|work=Ize Magazine}}</ref> It is also stated that their performance for Fan-dora's Box was \"another legendary stage\" due to the emotional acting by the members where they expressed \"anger in sadness\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=201910181351467619530_1|title=(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, '\ud038\ub364' 3\ucc28 \uacbd\uc5f0 '\uc2eb\ub2e4\uace0 \ub9d0\ud574' \uc720\ud29c\ube0c \uc870\ud68c\uc218 100\ub9cc\ubdf0 \ub3cc\ud30c|date=October 18, 2019|work=HeraldPop|language=ko}}</ref> (G)I-dle gave their last ''Queendom'' stage, \"[[Lion ((G)I-dle song)#Live performance|Lion]]\" with the ''Lion'' story which was narrated by Minnie, danced in golden robes ornately decorated with lion's mane and finished with a herd of lions [dancers] following (G)I-dle to the six thrones. The stage was described as \"a world-class stage\" and \"a legendary stage\".<ref>{{cite web|title='\ud038\ub364' (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uc601\ud654\uac19\uc740 \ud53c\ub0a0\ub808\u2026\"\uc774 \uc18c\ub140\ub294, LION\" (\uc601\uc0c1)|url=http://www.newstomato.com/ReadNews.aspx?no=930382|publisher=News Tomato|author=Kim Hee-kyung|date=November 1, 2019}}</ref> This resulted in winning  several performance awards including [[Golden Disc Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=201911271338474996408_1|work=HeraldPop|author=Kim Na-yul|date=November 27, 2019|title='2019 AAA' (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, AAA \uadf8\ub974\ubd80\uc0c1 \uc218\uc0c1..\"\ub354 \uc88b\uc740 \ubaa8\uc2b5\uc73c\ub85c \ubcf4\ub2f5\"|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=202001051655489275771_1|script-title=ko:[2020 \uace8\ub4e0\ub514\uc2a4\ud06c]\uc544\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub85c\u00b7(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \ubca0\uc2a4\ud2b8\ud37c\ud3ec\uba3c\uc2a4\uc0c1 \"\uc0c8\ud574 \ucd9c\ubc1c\ubd80\ud130 \uac10\uc0ac\"|date=January 5, 2020|work=HeraldPop|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tfmusicawards.com/winner_2nd_tf.html|title=WINNER 2019 THE FACT MUSIC AWARDS|work=The Fact Music Award|date=March 16, 2020|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n== Impact ==\nThe group was recognized for its brand recognition and marketing power, having topped the \"Girl Group Brand Power Ranking\" published by the Korean Business Research Institute. In 2018, they ranked #1 for June and September.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rekorea.net/bbs/board.php?bo_table=repu4&wr_id=256|title=[\ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc\ud3c9\ud310] \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc 2018\ub144 6\uc6d4 \ube45\ub370\uc774\ud130 \ubd84\uc11d...1\uc704 (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4|publisher=Korea Reputation Research Institute|date=June 9, 2018}}</ref> Their highest brand reputation index was in September 2018.<ref name=\"\uc5ec\uc790\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc\ud3c9\ud310 1\uc704 \ub4f1\uadf9 '\ud038\ub364' \ud6a8\uacfc\">{{cite news|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2019101310271318907|title=(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc\ud3c9\ud310 1\uc704 \ub4f1\uadf9 \"'\ud038\ub364' \ud6a8\uacfc\"|publisher=Star News|date=October 13, 2019}}</ref> (G)I-dle has been dubbed the \"monster rookie\" of 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=201805251656197111616_1|title='\ubba4\uc9c1\ubc45\ud06c' (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uad34\ubb3c \uc2e0\uc778\uc758 \uc139\uc2dc+\uace0\ud639 'LATATA'|work=HeraldPop|publisher=Ko Myung-jin|date=May 25, 2018|access-date=October 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://star.hankookilbo.com/News/Read/201901071602365871?did=NA&dtype=&dtypecode=&prnewsid=|title=(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uc2e0\uc778\uc0c1 5\uad00\uc655 \ub2ec\uc131...\u20192018 \uad34\ubb3c \uc2e0\uc778\u2019 \uc785\uc99d|work=Hankook Ilbo|publisher=Kim Han-na|date=January 7, 2019|access-date=October 20, 2019}}</ref> [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] ranked them at the top of its list as the best new K-pop group of 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8491744/best-new-k-pop-acts-2018|title=10 Best New K-Pop Acts of 2018|website=Billboard|date=December 29, 2018|access-date=July 24, 2019}}</ref> It was reported that Cube's music sales in 2018 increased by 58% to \u20a98.8 billion due to the popularity of (G)I-dle's \"Latata\" and \"Hann (\u4e00)\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.edaily.co.kr/news/read?newsId=03227526622394784&mediaCodeNo=257&OutLnkChk=Y|title=\ud050\ube0c\uc5d4\ud130 \uc9c0\ub09c\ud574 \ub9e4\ucd9c 358\uc5b5\uc6d0\u2026\uc0c1\uc7a5 \uc774\ud6c4 \ucd5c\ub300 \uc2e4\uc801 \ub2ec\uc131|trans-title=Cube Entertainment last year revenue of KRW 35.8 billion\u2026 Achieve maximum performance|work=EDaily|author=Kim Sung-hoon|date=February 27, 2019|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, (G)I-dle gained more recognition in the general public after appearing on ''[[Queendom (TV series)|Queendom]]''.<ref name=\"\uc5ec\uc790\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc\ud3c9\ud310 1\uc704 \ub4f1\uadf9 '\ud038\ub364' \ud6a8\uacfc\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://kenh14.vn/gi-dle-thong-tri-top-trending-voi-san-khau-cung-loat-than-thai-hoi-huom-kinh-di-20191018000146858.chn|title=(G)I-DLE th\u1ed1ng tr\u1ecb top trending v\u1edbi s\u00e2n kh\u1ea5u c\u00f9ng lo\u1ea1t th\u1ea7n th\u00e1i h\u01a1i h\u01b0\u1edbm kinh d\u1ecb|publisher=kenh14|author=Hoang Chi|date=October 18, 2019|language=vi}}</ref> The performance of their finale song \"Lion\" was considered as one of K-pop's biggest moments of 2019 by [[CTV News]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Somos |first1=Christy |title=These are some of K-pop's biggest moments of 2019 |url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/entertainment/these-are-some-of-k-pop-s-biggest-moments-of-2019-1.4738811 |website=CTVNews |accessdate=January 6, 2020 |language=en |date=December 20, 2019}}</ref> This resulted in them topping the \"Girl Group Brand Power Ranking\" for two consecutive months, in October and November 2019, respectively.<ref name=\"2nd\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://enews24.tving.com/news/article?nsID=1331406|title=(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, '\ud038\ub364' \uacbd\uc5f0\uace1 '\uc2eb\ub2e4\uace0 \ub9d0\ud574'\ub85c 100\ub9cc\ubdf0 \ub3cc\ud30c '\ud6c4\ub048'|author=Kim Ji-yeon|date=October 18, 2019|work=eNews24|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cnews.thebigdata.co.kr/view.php?ud=20191013100321789607d270612f_23|title=\uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc\ud3c9\ud310 10\uc6d4 \ube45\ub370\uc774\ud130 \ubd84\uc11d 1\uc704\ub294 (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4... 2\uc704 \ud2b8\uc640\uc774\uc2a4 ...|author=Kim Soo-ah|date=October 13, 2019|work=The Big Data News|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvdaily.asiae.co.kr/read.php3?aid=15733474531505465010#rs|title='\ud038\ub364 \ud6a8\uacfc' (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, 11\uc6d4 \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc\ud3c9\ud310 1\uc704|author=Hwang Seo-yeon|date=November 10, 2019|work=TvDaily|language=ko}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' India included \"Lion\" in their list of the 10 Best K-Pop Music Videos of 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rollingstoneindia.com/10-best-k-pop-music-videos-of-2019/|author=Riddhi Chakraborty|date=December 30, 2019|accessdate=January 8, 2020|title=10 Best K-Pop Music Videos of 2019|work=Rolling Stone India}}</ref> The song was considered as \"one of the most visceral tracks of 2019\" and was listed number one out of 920 songs released in 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=The 25 Best K-pop Songs of 2019: Critics' Picks|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/international/8547126/the-25-best-k-pop-songs-of-2019-critics-picks|publisher=Billboard|date=December 29, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\uacb0\uc0b0 2019 : \ucd5c\uace0\uc758 \ub178\ub798|trans-title=Closing 2019: best songs|url=http://idology.kr/12885|publisher=Idology|date=February 11, 2020}}</ref> In January 2020, (G)I-dle were voted as the Most Anticipated Singers/Groups in 2020 based on surveys of several Korean music agencies, broadcasting and program officials, composers and popular music critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news1.kr/articles/?3807390|title=[\uc2e0\ub144\ud2b9\uc9d1] \uc804\ubb38\uac00 21\uc778 \uc120\uc815, 2020 \uac00\uc7a5 \uae30\ub300\ub418\ub294 \uac00\uc218\ub294|trans-title=[New Year Special] 21 Experts, 2020 Most Expected Singers|date=January 4, 2020|work=News1|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2019123108275558313|title=\uac00\uc694 \uad00\uacc4\uc790 \uc120\uc815 2020 \ud65c\uc57d \uae30\ub300\ub418\ub294 \uadf8\ub8f9\uc740?\u2466[2020 \u2606\uc2e0\ub144\uae30\ud68d]|date=January 3, 2020|work=Star News|language=ko}}</ref> In February 2020, the group achieved number 1 in brand power with the most-interacted topics \"Lion\" and world tour.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rekorea.net/bbs/board.php?bo_table=repu4&wr_id=453|title=\t[\ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc\ud3c9\ud310] \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc 2020\ub144 2\uc6d4 \ube45\ub370\uc774\ud130 \ubd84\uc11d\uacb0\uacfc...1\uc704 (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, 2\uc704 \ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3, 3\uc704 \uc774\ub2ec\uc758 |date=February 9, 2020|work=Korea Reputation|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n===Guinness World Record===\n(G)I-dle achieved a new [[Guinness World Record]] with [[#Music Content Company|1theK]] record challenge ''Kkinness Challenge'' on episode 4.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1-3r-7CGOcY|title=(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4 \uc2e0\uae30\ub85d\ud83d\udc51 \ud50c\ub809\uc2a4 \ud55c \ud604\uc7a5! (\uc785.\ud2c0.\ub9c9\ud83d\ude4a) (G)I-DLE \ub07c\ub124\uc2a4\ucd0c EP.4 KKINNESS CHALLENGE LION Uh-Oh|date=March 24, 2020|publisher=1theK Originals - \uc6d0\ub354\ucf00\uc774 \uc624\ub9ac\uc9c0\ub110}}</ref> ''Kkinness Challenge'' is an 'Idol Guinness Challenge' that contains the process by which an idol group enters Kkinness Village, an athlete village designed to challenge the world record of extreme events. In the video released on March 24, 2020, the group succeeded in achieving a new world record for the \"Fastest time to hang up five T-shirts\" in 25.41 seconds; the previous record-holder was held by Kaito Kozumi in 27.93 seconds.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rpm9.com/news/article.html?id=20200325090008|title='\ub07c\ub124\uc2a4\ucd0c' (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uae00\ub85c\ubc8c \uc774\uc0c9 \uc2e0\uae30\ub85d\ub2ec\uc131\u2026'\uc637\uac78\uc774\uc5d0 \ud2f0\uc154\uce20 5\uc7a5 \ube68\ub9ac\uac78\uae30' \ubbf8\uc158\uc131\uacf5|trans-title='Kinness Village' (G)I-dle, Achieve Global New Record\u2026 Success of 'Five pieces of T-shirts on hangers'|author=Park Dong-sun|date=March 25, 2020|work=RPM9}}</ref> On the first attempt, member Soyeon scored 28.34 seconds, which was close to the Guinness record, but unfortunately failed. Subsequently, member Shuhua, took the challenge and recorded 26.81 seconds breaking the world record. However, Soyeon who re-challenged, recorded 25.41 seconds and breaking the previous record by Shuhua. The record will be recognized as the official world record by the world's top 3 record certification agency, Supertalent World Record, and will proceed with the official procedure for Guinness listing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sports.donga.com/ent/article/all/20200325/100337634/1|title=(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \uae30\ub124\uc2a4 \uc138\uacc4\uc2e0\uae30\ub85d \uacbd\uc2e0\u2192\uc6d4\ub4dc\ud074\ub798\uc2a4 \ub4f1\uadf9|trans-title=(G)I-dle, break the world record for Guinness \u2192 World Class|author=Hong Se-young|date=March 25, 2020|work=Sports Donga}}</ref>\n\n== Ambassadorship ==\n[[Seoul Capital Area|Seoul Metropolitan City]] appointed (G)I-dle as the city's goodwill ambassadors alongside [[Yura (South Korean singer)|Yura]], [[Park Jin-Hee]], and eight other nominees. They will hold the title \"City Ambassadors\" for two years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cstimes.com/?mod=news&act=articleView&idxno=291618|title=\uac78\uc2a4\ub370\uc774 \uc720\ub77c-\ubc30\uc6b0 \ubc15\uc9c4\ud76c, \uc138\uacc4\uc5d0 \uc11c\uc6b8\uc2dc \uc54c\ub9b0\ub2e4|work=CSTimes|date=December 6, 2018}}</ref> On the 10th annual Children's Diabetes Celebration Festival held at Lotte World Underground Kingdom in [[Eunpyeong District|Eunpyeong-gu]], Seoul, they were awarded as the new ambassador for Korean Children's Diabetes Association.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0004026271|title=(\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \ud55c\uad6d\uc18c\uc544\ub2f9\ub1e8\uc778\ud611\ud68c \ud64d\ubcf4\ub300\uc0ac \uc704\ucd09 [\uacf5\uc2dd]|work=Osen|date=June 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Endorsements ==\nIn 2019, (G)I-dle became the first Korean girl group to endorse with Kaja, a beauty brand co-created by [[Sephora]] and Memebox to create a new form combining K-beauty and K-pop.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wsobi.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=70250|title=\uc5ec\uc790\uc544\uc774\ub4e4\u2019 \uce74\uc790 \ubaa8\ub378\ub85c \uc120\uc815\u2026 K\ubdf0\ud2f0&K\ud31d \uc2dc\ub108\uc9c0 \uae30\ub300|trans-title='(G)I-dle' selected as Kaja model\u2026 Expect K Beauty & K-Pop Synergy|work=Wsobi|author=Lee Ji-eun|date=March 1, 2019|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> Through the partnership, ''To Neverland'' reality TV series and \"Senorita\" music video were released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hypebae.com/2019/2/k-pop-girl-group-gi-dle-announces-kaja-partnership-with-senorita-music-video|title=K-POP GIRL GROUP (G)I-DLE ANNOUNCES KAJA PARTNERSHIP WITH \"SENORITA\" MUSIC VIDEO|work=HypeBae|author=Teresa Lam|date=February 26, 2019|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n\n(G)I-dle were selected as Akiii Classic's new model in 2020 to reinforce the sensitivity of [[generation Z|Gen Z]] culture and trend pioneering the brand image.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.khan.co.kr/entertainment/sk_index.html?art_id=202003041029003&sec_id=540101&pt=nv|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd] (\uc5ec\uc790)\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \u2018\uc544\ud0a4\ud074\ub798\uc2dd\u2019 \uc0c8 \ubaa8\ub378 \ubc1c\ud0c1\u2026\ub300\uc138 \ud589\ubcf4 \uc774\uc5b4\uac04\ub2e4|work=Sports Khan|author=Yoo Ha-eun|date=March 4, 2020}}</ref> In early April 2020, (G)I-dle was revealed as a promotional model for South Korea biggest contact lens brand, LensMe. A representative from LensMe explained that the group's unique music and charismatic stage performances matched well with their 'Basic, Trendy, Easy' company image.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lens-me.com/shopinfo/LENSME_MUSE.html|title=LENS-ME WITH (G)I-DLE|publisher=LensMe|date=April 1, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kgdm.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=688967|title=\uc5ec\uc790\uc544\uc774\ub4e4, \ucf58\ud0dd\ud2b8\ub80c\uc988 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc \uc804\uc18d \ubaa8\ub378\ub85c \ubc1c\ud0c1|work=Gyeonggi Provincial Daily|author=Lee Da-yeon|date=April 1, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Main|(G)I-dle discography}}\n{{See also|List of songs recorded by (G)I-dle}}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n'''Korean releases'''\n* ''[[I Am ((G)I-dle EP)|I Am]]'' (2018)\n* ''[[I Made]]'' (2019)\n* ''[[I Trust]]'' (2020)\n{{col-2}}\n'''Japanese releases'''\n* ''[[Latata (EP)|Latata]]'' (2019)\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Concerts and tours==\n\n===Headlining tours===\n* ''(G)I-dle World Tour I-Land: Who Am I Tour'' (2020)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zenithnews.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=137537|title