)\n| format     = [[CD single]]\n| recorded   = 2002\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=3|s=36}}\n| label      = \n*[[Bertelsmann Music Group|BMG]]\n*[[S.M. Entertainment]]\n| writer     = \n*[[Wayne Hector]]\n*[[Steve Mac]]\n| producer   = \n*[[Lee Soo Man]]\n*Steve Mac\n| chronology = [[BoA]] singles\n| prev_track =\n| track_no   =\n| next_track =\n| misc        = {{External music video|{{YouTube|T1W8fWzfMk|\"Flying Without Wings (featuring BoA)\"}}}}\n}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Flying Without Wings\n| cover      = Westlife feat. Cristian Castro - Flying Without Wings.jpg\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| type       = promo\n| artist     = [[Westlife]] featuring [[Cristian Castro]]\n| album      = [[Unbreakable: The Greatest Hits Volume 1]] (Spanish/Mexican edition)\n| released   = {{Start date|2002}} (Mexico)\n| format     = [[CD single]], digital download\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=3|s=36}}\n| label      =\n| writer     = \n*[[Wayne Hector]]\n*[[Steve Mac]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_track =\n| track_no   =\n| next_track =\n| misc        = {{External music video|{{YouTube|fZOW8ZuLG2o|\"Flying Without Wings (featuring Cristian Castro)\"}}}}\n}}\n\nIn 2002, as part of the promotion of their album ''[[Unbreakable: The Greatest Hits Volume 1]]'', the song was re-recorded as a [[duet]] with [[Mexico|Mexican]] singer [[Cristian Castro]] and [[South Korea]]n pop singer, [[BoA]]. Each duet was included on the Spanish & Asian editions of the album. Both duets were also released as singles in their two respective regions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eil.com/shop/moreinfo.asp?catalogid=239371 |title=Westlife Flying Without Wings Mexico Promo 5\" CD SINGLE (239371) |publisher=Eil.com |date=2003-03-12 |accessdate=2012-01-06}}</ref>\n\n===Track listing===\n* '''Mexico'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eil.com/shop/moreinfo.asp?catalogid=244450 |title=Westlife Flying Without Wings Mexico 5\" CD SINGLE (244450) |publisher=Eil.com |date=2003-04-24 |accessdate=2012-01-06}}</ref>\n# \"Flying Without Wings\" <small>(Duet with Cristian Castro)</small> - 3:35\n# \"Never Knew I Was Losing You\" - 4:09\n* '''Asia'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eil.com/shop/moreinfo.asp?catalogid=255411 |title=Westlife Flying Without Wings Japan Promo 5\" CD SINGLE (255411) |publisher=Eil.com |date=2003-08-15 |accessdate=2012-01-06}}</ref>\n# \"Flying Without Wings\" <small>(Duet with BoA)</small> - 3:35\n# \"Never Knew I Was Losing You\" - 4:09\n\n==Live version==\nIn 2004, as part of the promotion for their ''[[Turnaround Tour]]'', the band released the live version of the song. It was recorded during their tour in [[Ericsson Globe|Stockholm Globe Arena]]. Their live version peaked at number one in UK Singles Chart and was the first ever number one in the UK downloads chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/3617020.stm|title=Westlife top first download chart|date=1 September 2004|publisher=|via=news.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>\n\n===Track listing===\n* '''UK'''\n# \"Flying Without Wings\" (Live)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.westlife.com/global/discography/all/all/all/flying_without_wings_live#flash-nav|title=Westlife|website=www.westlife.com}}{{Dead link|date=December 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n===Chart performance===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Charts (2004)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n|UK Download Singles ([[UK Singles Chart|Official Charts Company]])\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|}\n\n==Video album==\nA karaoke version of \"Flying Without Wings\" was released on DVD in 2000 and debuted at number one. It includes easy to read lyrics, photographs & interactive menus, picture sleeve. It has a running time of 45 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eil.com/shop/moreinfo.asp?catalogid=246048 |title=Westlife Flying Without Wings Karaoke UK DIGITAL VERSATILE DISC (246048) |publisher=Eil.com |date=2003-05-07 |accessdate=2012-01-06}}</ref>\n\n===Track listing===\n# \"Swear It Again\"\n# \"If I Let You Go\"\n# \"Flying Without Wings\"\n# \"Fool Again\"\n# \"Seasons in the Sun\"\n# \"I Have a Dream\"\n# \"More Than Words\"\n# \"Against All Odds\"\n\n===CD production===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"|width=100%\n|-\n|<small>Arranged by (strings)</small>\n|<small>: ''[[Richard Niles]]''</small>\n|-\n|<small>Arranged by (vocals)</small>\n|<small>: ''[[Steve Mac]], [[Wayne Hector]]''</small>\n|-\n|<small>Arranged by, mixed by</small>\n|<small>: ''Steve Mac''</small>\n|-\n|<small>Artwork by (design)</small>\n|<small>: ''Root''</small>\n|-\n|<small>Photography</small>\n|<small>: ''Brian Aris''</small>\n|-\n|<small>Bass guitar</small>\n|<small>: ''Steve Pearce''</small>\n|-\n|<small>Guitar</small>\n|<small>: ''Paul Gendler''</small>\n|-\n|<small>Performer (Choir Md)</small>\n|<small>: ''Benny Diggs''</small>\n|-\n|<small>Engineer (Mix)</small>\n|<small>: ''Matt Howe''</small>\n|-\n|<small>Engineer, Programmed by</small>\n|<small>: ''Chris Laws''</small>\n|-\n|<small>Other (management)</small>\n|<small>: ''[[Louis Walsh]], [[Ronan Keating]]''</small>\n|}\n\n==Tours performed at==\n*[[Where Dreams Come True Tour]] (2001)\n*[[World of Our Own Tour]] (2002)\n*[[Unbreakable Tour (Westlife concert tour)|Unbreakable Tour]] (2003)\n*[[Turnaround Tour]] (2004)\n*[[Number Ones Tour (Westlife concert tour)|The Number Ones Tour]] (2005)\n*[[Face to Face Tour]] (2006)\n*[[The Love Tour (Westlife concert tour)|The Love Tour]] (2007)\n*[[Back Home Tour]] (2008)\n*[[Where We Are Tour (Westlife)|Where We Are Tour]] (2010)\n*[[Gravity Tour]] (2011)\n*[[Greatest Hits Tour (Westlife)|Greatest Hits Tour]] (2012)\n*[[Shane Filan#Tours|You and Me Tour]] ([[Shane Filan]]) (2014)\n*Boyzlife Tour (Boyzlife) (2017)\n*[[The Twenty Tour]] (2019)\n\n==Other appearances==\nThe Westlife song has appeared in the 2000 [[Warner Bros. Pictures]] film ''[[Pok\u00e9mon: The Movie 2000]]'' as the final song of the credits in the film and on the official movie soundtrack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/album/original-soundtrack/pokemon-2000-the-power-of-one/435355 |title=Pokemon 2000: The Power of One- Original Soundtrack;|publisher=Billboard.com|date= |accessdate=2012-03-13}}</ref> It is also the only Westlife song that coincidently coincided with the original Japanese release date of the ''Pok\u00e9mon'' movie sequel. It also featured in the 2000 Australian film ''[[The Magic Pudding (film)|The Magic Pudding]]'' and 2000 French film ''[[Archibald the Koala|Archibald the Koala: The Movie]]''.\n\nOn 12 May 2018, the song was performed on Korean music programme '[[Immortal Songs 2]]' by [[Ali (South Korean singer)|Ali]] who placed second place that night. Band member [[Shane Filan]] was the featured 'Legend' and judged the participants.\n\n==Ruben Studdard version==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Flying Without Wings\n| cover      = FlyingWithoutWings.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Ruben Studdard]]\n| album      =\n| released   = {{start date|2003|6|10|df=y}}\n| format     = [[CD single]]\n| recorded   = 2003\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = \n*[[Urban contemporary]]\n*[[contemporary R&B]]\n| length     =\n| label      = [[J Records|J]]\n| writer     = \n*[[Wayne Hector]]\n*[[Steve Mac]]\n| producer   = \n*[[The Underdogs (duo)|The Underdogs]]\n*Face\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Superstar (Delaney and Bonnie song)#Ruben Studdard version|Superstar]]\n| next_year  = 2003\n}}\n\n\"Flying Without Wings\" was covered by ''[[American Idol]]'' winner [[Ruben Studdard]] as his debut single in 2003.  The single was released on June 10 and charted at number two on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] on June 28, behind  \"[[This Is the Night (Clay Aiken song)|This Is the Night]]\" by [[Clay Aiken]]. \"Flying Without Wings\" also gained attention on the [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Singles & Tracks]] chart, peaking at number thirteen, while it reached number 27 on the adult contemporary chart. It was also released in [[New Zealand]] and reached number two behind Clay Aiken. The single had sold 751,000 copies through December 2006. This version of the song also appears on the game [[Karaoke Revolution|Karaoke Revolution Presents: American Idol]].\n\n===Track listing===\n# \"Flying Without Wings\" the love you can see the same time as the first time in the future and the other is a great way to get the best out of the way and I have to say that I am not a fan of the most important thing to do is to provide an opportunity to make 88798lonu\n# \"[[Superstar (Delaney and Bonnie song)|Superstar]]\"\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{YouTube|G1LEISP6e9c|\"Flying Without Wings\" - Westlife Official Music Video}}\n*{{YouTube|-T1W8fWzfMk|\"Flying Without Wings\" - Westlife with BoA Official Music Video}}\n*{{YouTube|0udkZKyRAwY|\"Flying Without Wings\" - Westlife with Cristian Castro Official Music Video}}\n*{{YouTube|ZgiX33AVqA8|\"Flying Without Wings\" - Ruben Studdard Official Music Video}}\n*[http://www.westlife.com Official Westlife website]\n\n{{Navboxes|list1=\n{{Westlife songs}}\n{{Ruben Studdard}}\n{{American Idol}}\n{{American Idol 2}}\n{{BoA singles}}\n{{Cristian Castro}}}}\n\n[[Category:1990s ballads]]\n[[Category:1999 singles]]\n[[Category:2003 singles]]\n[[Category:Westlife songs]]\n[[Category:Ruben Studdard songs]]\n[[Category:Delta Goodrem songs]]\n[[Category:BoA songs]]\n[[Category:Cristian Castro songs]]\n[[Category:Pop ballads]]\n[[Category:UK Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Irish Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Steve Mac]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Wayne Hector]]\n[[Category:Songs written for animated films]]\n[[Category:Songs from Pok\u00e9mon]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Steve Mac]]\n[[Category:1999 songs]]\n[[Cat